      "content": "So if the studies mostly show a modest positive effect on GDP, doesn't that mean the \"anti\" side is mostly just focused on anecdotal or localized issues rather than the actual macro data? It feels like the pro-immigration side is backed by the hard numbers while the other side is more about political concerns.",
